HEADWORD: Lingel
<hw>Lin"gel</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧"g⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ligneul</ets>, dim. of L. <ets>linea</ets> a linen thread.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A shoemaker's thread.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A little tongue or thong of leather; a lacing for
belts.</def> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lingenberry</ent>⟦br⟧
